theorem Topology.interior_diff_subset_diff_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A \ B) ⊆ A \ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  -- `x` lies in `A \ B`.
  have hxAB : x ∈ A \ B := interior_subset hx
  have hxA : x ∈ A := hxAB.1
  -- We will show that `x ∉ closure B`.
  have hx_not_clB : x ∉ closure B := by
    by_contra hCl
    -- Since `x ∈ closure B`, every open neighbourhood of `x` meets `B`.
    -- Consider the open neighbourhood `interior (A \ B)` of `x`.
    have h_nonempty : (interior (A \ B) ∩ B).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hCl (interior (A \ B)) isOpen_interior hx
    -- But `interior (A \ B)` is disjoint from `B`.
    have h_empty : (interior (A \ B) ∩ B) = (∅ : Set X) := by
      ext y
      constructor
      · intro hy
        have : y ∈ A \ B := interior_subset hy.1
        exact (this.2) hy.2
      · intro hy
        cases hy
    -- Contradiction.
    have : (∅ : Set X).Nonempty := by
      simpa [h_empty] using h_nonempty
    exact this.elim
  exact And.intro hxA hx_not_clB
